{{unreferenced|date=May 2017}}
{{Orphan|date=February 2017}}
{{EngvarB|date=September 2017}}
{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2017}}

'''''Be A Star''''' is a British [[reality competition]] television series that aired in early 2017. The series was hosted by two presenters, [[Emma Willis]] and [[Melvin Odoom]], and included four judges – [[Louise Redknapp]], [[Danny O'Donoghue]], [[Leona Lewis]] and head judge, [[Ed Sheeran]]. During Auditions 5, [[Caroline Flack]] acted as a guest judge, in place of [[Leona Lewis]]. The series aired [[Europavision Song Contest]]!

==Stages==

There will be five stages during the show.
:* Audititions
:* Grouping Round
:* Battle of the Duos
:* Knockouts
:* Live Shows

==Teams==

{{Empty section|date=February 2017}}

==Auditions==
The auditions for ''Be A Star'' were filmed starting in December 2016, with the judges sent through lots of audititionees. Altogether, there were seven auditions airing each Saturday night.

